<p class="p">Monsoon rainfall is controlled by both moisture supply (thermodynamics) and atmospheric circulation (dynamics). What are their relative roles in shaping the responses in Figures 
 <xref rid="grl56839-fig-0001" ref-type="fig" class="xref">1</xref>a and 
 <xref rid="grl56839-fig-0001" ref-type="fig" class="xref">1</xref>b? We use the atmospheric moisture budget analysis to quantify the thermodynamic and dynamic mechanisms contributing to the rainfall changes, as illustrated in Figure 
 <xref rid="grl56839-fig-0002" ref-type="fig" class="xref">2</xref>. Changes in the column‐integrated mean moisture convergence ( 
